message.content:
Create these files in /sessions/kind-hopeful-brahmagupta/mnt/outputs/stat-study-app/data/:

FILE 1: topics-2kyu.js - Export an array of 5 topic objects for 2級 level statistics. Each follows the same format as the jun1kyu topic files (id, name, icon, sections array with title/content). Topics:
1. id:"descriptive", name:"記述統計", icon:"📊" - sections: データの種類と尺度, 代表値(mean/median/mode), 散布度(variance/SD/IQR/CV)
2. id:"probability", name:"確率", icon:"🎲" - sections: 確率の基本(axioms/addition/conditional/Bayes), 確率変数と確率分布(discrete/continuous, E[X], V[X])
3. id:"distribution", name:"確率分布", icon:"📈" - sections: 離散型分布(binomial/Poisson/geometric), 連続型分布(normal/t/chi-squared/F, CLT)
4. id:"inference", name:"推測統計", icon:"🔍" - sections: 点推定と区間推定(unbiasedness/consistency/efficiency, CI formulas), 仮説検定(procedure, Type I/II errors, power)
5. id:"regression", name:"回帰分析", icon:"📉" - sections: 単回帰分析(OLS, R², t-test for coefficient)

Make content detailed (500-1000 chars per section), in Japanese, with formulas.
Export as: `export const topics2kyu = [...]`

FILE 2: topics-1kyu.js - Export an array of 2 topic objects for 1級:
1. id:"measure_theory", name:"測度論的確率論", icon:"∫" - sections: σ-加法族と測度, ルベーグ積分と期待値, 収束の概念(a.s./probability/Lp/distribution)
2. id:"asymptotic", name:"漸近理論", icon:"∞" - sections: 大数の法則(weak/strong), 中心極限定理, デルタ法, 最尤推定量の漸近性質

Export as: `export const topics1kyu = [...]`

FILE 3: levels.js - Export level definitions:
```javascript
export const LEVELS = {
  "2kyu": { name: "2級", color: "blue", description: "大学基礎レベルの統計学" },
  "jun1kyu": { name: "準1級", color: "purple", description: "応用的な統計手法（とけたろう講座準拠）" },
  "1kyu": { name: "1級", color: "red", description: "高度な理論・応用" },
};
```

FILE 4: index.js - Central data index that imports everything and re-exports:
```javascript
import { LEVELS } from './levels.js';
import { topics2kyu } from './topics-2kyu.js';
import { topicMle } from './topics-mle.js';
import { topicNonparametric } from './topics-nonparametric.js';
import { topicMarkov } from './topics-markov.js';
import { topicBrownian } from './topics-brownian.js';
import { topicTimeseries } from './topics-timeseries.js';
import { topicCluster } from './topics-cluster.js';
import { topicPca } from './topics-pca.js';
import { topicFactor } from './topics-factor.js';
import { topicAnova } from './topics-anova.js';
import { topicSampling } from './topics-sampling.js';
import { topicConditional } from './topics-conditional.js';
import { topicQualreg } from './topics-qualreg.js';
import { topicSurvival } from './topics-survival.js';
import { topicMgf } from './topics-mgf.js';
import { topicPoissonProcess } from './topics-poisson-process.js';
import { topicBayes } from './topics-bayes.js';
import { topicMvnormal } from './topics-mvnormal.js';
import { topicIncomplete } from './topics-incomplete.js';
import { topicMultreg } from './topics-multreg.js';
import { topicContingency } from './topics-contingency.js';
import { topicGraphical } from './topics-graphical.js';
import { topicOtherMv } from './topics-other-mv.js';
import { topicDiscriminant } from './topics-discriminant.js';
import { topics1kyu } from './topics-1kyu.js';
import { questions2kyu } from './questions-2kyu.js';
import { questionsJun1kyu } from './questions-jun1kyu.js';
import { questions1kyu } from './questions-1kyu.js';

const topicsJun1kyu = [
  topicMle, topicNonparametric, topicMarkov, topicBrownian,
  topicTimeseries, topicCluster, topicPca, topicFactor,
  topicAnova, topicSampling, topicConditional, topicQualreg,
  topicSurvival, topicMgf, topicPoissonProcess, topicBayes,
  topicMvnormal, topicIncomplete, topicMultreg, topicContingency,
  topicGraphical, topicOtherMv, topicDiscriminant
];

export const TOPICS = {
  "2kyu": topics2kyu,
  "jun1kyu": topicsJun1kyu,
  "1kyu": topics1kyu,
};

export const QUESTIONS = {
  "2kyu": questions2kyu,
  "jun1kyu": questionsJun1kyu,
  "1kyu": questions1kyu,
};

export { LEVELS };
```

Make sure to check what export names the existing topic files actually use (read them first with the Read tool) before writing the index.

